  "summary": {
    "en": [
      "<p>The print is the earliest known published image of Sidi Bashir Mosque in Northwestern India. Centered on the twin prayer towers of the mosque, notable for how they shake in tandem when the motion of ascending the tower before calling for prayer shakes the minaret.<br>British artist and Captain, Robert Grindlay painted the mosque while traveling India with the Bombay army. The print, first appearing in Scenery, costumes and architecture, chiefly on the western side of India, shows the mosque in a documentary fashion, with even the details on the walls of the mosque being preserved for future viewers.</p>"
    ]
  },
